---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About - Martin M. E." description="Data Engineer, builder, and relentless learner. Based in Monterrey, Mexico." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="glass-card">
				<h1>About me</h1>

				<p>
					I'm Martin, a Data Engineer at <a href="https://caylent.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Caylent</a>.
					I build cloud infrastructure and data systems on AWS. I'm based in Monterrey, Mexico.
					Spanish is my native language, and I'm fully proficient in English.
				</p>

				<h2>What I believe</h2>

				<p>
					Technology is one of the most powerful forces humanity has ever created. It has reduced
					disease, scarcity, and war. But power without direction is dangerous, and not all
					progress is equal. I believe the most important question in engineering is not
					"can we build this?" but "should we, and for whom?"
				</p>

				<p>
					I care about animal welfare. Factory farming is one of the largest sources of suffering
					on the planet and it scaled with technology, not despite it. I care about the responsible
					development of AI, a technology powerful enough to reshape civilization and one that
					deserves careful, honest thinking about alignment and values. I care about open data
					and civic infrastructure, especially in Mexico where public data is abundant but
					inaccessible.
				</p>

				<p>
					I believe the people who build things have a responsibility to think about what those
					things do in the world. Not just whether they work. Whether they help.
				</p>

				<h2>How I think</h2>

				<p>
					I think in tradeoffs. There's rarely an absolute best option in engineering, only
					the right option for <em>this</em> context, <em>these</em> constraints, <em>this</em> team.
					I care about understanding why a solution works, not just how to implement it.
				</p>

				<p>
					I believe in breaking problems into smaller parts, thinking in diagrams, and always
					delivering something. If a task isn't practical yet, I build a document. If I don't
					know something, I go learn it. My approach is: roadmaps, checklists, requirements.
					Then iterate.
				</p>

				<p>
					I think aesthetics are a core element of engineering. A well-designed interface reduces
					cognitive load. A beautifully structured codebase is easier to maintain. The form
					and the function are inseparable.
				</p>

				<p>
					I'm deeply influenced by Martin Kleppmann's <em>Designing Data-Intensive Applications</em>
					and the philosophy that real engineering is about grabbing existing blocks and snapping
					them together to create something new. The superpower isn't genius. It's iteration.
				</p>

				<h2>What I do</h2>

				<p>
					My work lives at the intersection of data engineering and cloud architecture. I've worked
					on data warehouse migrations, OpenSearch implementations, Kubernetes-based data platforms,
					and analytics layers. I build data pipelines, design architectures, validate production
					systems, and help teams solve problems across the AWS ecosystem.
				</p>

				<h2>Beyond work</h2>

				<p>
					When I'm not engineering, I'm probably on my bike, reading, exploring ideas, or
					diving into whatever concept caught my curiosity this week. I care about mental health,
					continuous learning, and the effort of trying to leave things better than I found them.
				</p>

				<h2>This site</h2>

				<p>
					This website is deployed on AWS using S3, CloudFront, ACM, and Route 53, all managed
					with Terraform and deployed via GitHub Actions with OIDC authentication. No long-lived keys,
					no manual deploys, zero-trust CI/CD. The whole thing costs about $0.51/month.
				</p>

				<p>
					Built with <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>.
					Source on <a href="https://github.com/Martin-00/martinme.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
